                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/294: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-17T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 17, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3855. Your 4320, September 16. Kindly advise Department what articles if any it
                    is contemplated will be included in the International Tin Agreement calculated
                    to protect the interest of the peoples of importing and consuming countries, and
                    send text of same. Kindly advise the British Government that this Government
                    expects adequate opportunity to be consulted in regard to these clauses before
                    any agreement is put into effect.</p>
                <p>In this connection also kindly advise Department what arrangements are
                    contemplated for the accumulation of buffer stocks or reserves to take care of
                    shortages, emergencies, or unjustified price increases.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
